<arggraph id="micro_b041">
  <edu id="e1"><![CDATA[Secret services must be more tightly regulated]]></edu>
  <edu id="e2"><![CDATA[in order to prevent excessive surveillance.]]></edu>
  <edu id="e3"><![CDATA[After all, secret services tend to develop a life of their own (a state within a state),]]></edu>
  <edu id="e4"><![CDATA[which would be irresponsible for democratic states.]]></edu>
  <edu id="e5"><![CDATA[Besides, intelligence services intervene massively in the privacy of citizens]]></edu>
  <edu id="e6"><![CDATA[and must therefore be monitored more closely]]></edu>
  <edu id="e7"><![CDATA[to prevent abuse.]]></edu>
  <edu id="e8"><![CDATA[Parliamentary control however hampers the work of intelligence services]]></edu>
  <edu id="e9"><![CDATA[for it jeopardizes the secrecy and security of confidential data and informants.]]></edu>
